item.title: Mid afternoon in the arctic
item.description: I am a man with no refuge, A world that whispers death songs Echoing screams claw at my mind, Turning safety to dust, belonging to ash. Nights are a war zone inside my skull, Where voices chant of all my failings, Every fractured moment replayed, The fault lines of a broken home, A child born from pain and silence, Crushed beneath heavy shadows cast by those who judge. I bear the scars that history wrote for me, A living testament to wounds not mine to claim, Yet the world sees only the mark, the stain, A life unwelcome, a silent plea drowned in hate. Yet in this void where love retreats, I stand a flicker in the endless dark, Not an abomination, but a soul unyielding, Fighting the screams with every breath, Seeking a dawn beyond the storm’s cold roar. This is the voice of a man lost, yet unbroken, Wrestling with ghosts and clawing for peace, Holding onto the fragile thread of tomorrow, In a world eager to see him erased, He whispers back, “I am still here.”
